-- Indian shares surge to record closing high
-- By Indulal PM
-- Thu Jun 05, 2014 06:10AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, June 5 (Reuters) - Indian shares surged to a fresh closing high on Thursday on gains in resources stocks such as Sesa Sterlite due to continued optimism about a revival in the domestic economy.

The benchmark BSE index <.BSESN> provisionally closed 0.86 percent higher at 25,019.51, surpassing the earlier record set on Tuesday. The broader NSE index <.NSEI> gained 0.97 percent to 7,474.10, breaching Tuesday's record.